---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="How AdBunny's AI Banner Optimization Works"
  description="See exactly how AdBunny's single JS tag and AI optimization layer turn remnant ad inventory into revenue — step by step."
  keywords="how AI banner optimization works, ad tag integration, real-time banner optimization, ad monetization process"
>

<section class="pt-28 pb-12 max-md:pt-20">
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8">
    <div class="max-w-[44rem]">
      <h1 class="font-extrabold leading-[1.05] tracking-tight mb-4" style="font-size:clamp(2.25rem,5vw,3.5rem)">From empty ad slot to optimized revenue — step by step</h1>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">Four steps. One tag. Zero engineering lift.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="py-16 max-md:py-12">
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8">
    <div class="max-w-[56rem]">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-10 gap-y-16 max-md:gap-x-6 max-md:gap-y-10" style="color:var(--color-text)">
        <div class="text-[clamp(4rem,6vw,6rem)] font-extrabold leading-none tracking-tight" style="color:var(--color-text-tertiary);opacity:0.3">1</div>
        <div class="pt-3">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-2" style="color:var(--color-text)">Add the tag</h3>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">Paste a single JavaScript snippet into the pages or slots you want AdBunny to cover. No SDK, no server integration, no waterfall configuration.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-[clamp(4rem,6vw,6rem)] font-extrabold leading-none tracking-tight" style="color:var(--color-text-tertiary);opacity:0.3">2</div>
        <div class="pt-3">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-2" style="color:var(--color-text)">AdBunny evaluates available demand</h3>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">When a covered slot loads, AdBunny's optimization layer evaluates the banner demand available for that specific impression in real time.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-[clamp(4rem,6vw,6rem)] font-extrabold leading-none tracking-tight" style="color:var(--color-text-tertiary);opacity:0.3">3</div>
        <div class="pt-3">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-2" style="color:var(--color-text)">The AI selects the best-paying banner</h3>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">Rather than following a fixed, static call order, the system picks whichever available banner is likely to generate the most revenue for that impression, right now.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-[clamp(4rem,6vw,6rem)] font-extrabold leading-none tracking-tight" style="color:var(--color-text-tertiary);opacity:0.3">4</div>
        <div class="pt-3">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-2" style="color:var(--color-text)">The slot fills, you get paid</h3>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">The impression fills, and revenue starts flowing from inventory that used to sit empty or monetize at low, static rates.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="dark-noise py-24 max-md:py-16" style="background:var(--color-surface)">
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8" style="position:relative;z-index:2">
    <div class="max-w-[40rem]">
      <h2 class="text-[clamp(1.75rem,3vw,2.25rem)] font-bold leading-snug tracking-tight mb-8">What you don't have to do</h2>
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-5">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
          <span class="split-check"></span>
          <span class="text-base" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">No waterfall to build or maintain</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
          <span class="split-check"></span>
          <span class="text-base" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">No line items to configure</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
          <span class="split-check"></span>
          <span class="text-base" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">No manual optimization or A/B testing of network order</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
          <span class="split-check"></span>
          <span class="text-base" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">No conflict with your existing primary demand</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="py-24 max-md:py-16 text-center">
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8">
    <h2 class="text-[clamp(1.75rem,3vw,2.5rem)] font-bold tracking-tight mb-3">See it running on your own inventory</h2>
    <p class="text-base mb-8" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">One tag. Four steps. Revenue from inventory that used to sit empty.</p>
    <a href="/" class="btn btn-primary">Get Your JS Tag</a>
  </div>
</section>
</BaseLayout>
